// Scene Graph
// Defines all node types, visual properties, and the SceneGraph class that owns the node tree, variables, and component/instance relationships.
// synced: 2026-03-26T13:51:59Z

[Central data structure: SceneGraph holds a flat Map<id, SceneNode> plus parent/child links via parentId/childIds.
 Root is a FRAME named "Document"; pages are CANVAS children of root.
 Variables live in a separate Map; collections track active mode per collection.
 CONTAINER_TYPES: CANVAS, FRAME, GROUP, SECTION, COMPONENT, COMPONENT_SET, INSTANCE.]

FUNCTION createDefaultNode(type, overrides) -> SceneNode [2026-03-26]                EXPORT
  Constructs a fully-populated SceneNode with safe defaults (100x100, no fills,
  Inter 14px, layout NONE, etc.), merges overrides. Used everywhere a new node is created.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.constructor() [2026-03-26]
  Creates the root FRAME ("Document") and calls addPage("Page 1").

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.createNode(type, parentId, overrides) -> SceneNode [2026-03-26]
  Calls createDefaultNode, sets parentId, appends id to parent.childIds. Returns the new node.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.updateNode(id, changes) [2026-03-26]
  Shallow-merges changes onto the existing node via Object.assign.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.deleteNode(id) [2026-03-26]
  Removes node from parent.childIds, then recursively deletes all children, then deletes from map.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.reparentNode(nodeId, newParentId) [2026-03-26]
  Moves a node to a new parent while preserving its absolute visual position by converting
  coordinates relative to the new parent. Guards against reparenting into own descendants.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.reorderChild(nodeId, parentId, insertIndex) [2026-03-26]
  Removes node from its current parent and splices it into parentId.childIds at insertIndex.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.getAbsolutePosition(id) -> {x, y} [2026-03-26]
  Walks the parent chain summing x/y until reaching root or a CANVAS node.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.hitTest(px, py, scopeId?) -> SceneNode | null [2026-03-26]
  Shallow hit-test: treats COMPONENT/INSTANCE as opaque (returns the container, not a child).
  Delegates to hitTestChildren in non-deep mode.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.hitTestDeep(px, py, scopeId?) -> SceneNode | null [2026-03-26]
  Deep hit-test (double-click): recurses into COMPONENT/INSTANCE children.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.hitTestFrame(px, py, excludeIds, scopeId?) -> SceneNode | null [2026-03-26]
  Returns the deepest container node under the point, used to find drop targets.
  Skips nodes in excludeIds.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.cloneTree(sourceId, parentId, overrides?) -> SceneNode | null [2026-03-26]
  Deep-clones a subtree under a new parent, assigning fresh IDs. Used for copy/paste and instance creation.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.createInstance(componentId, parentId, overrides?) -> SceneNode | null [2026-03-26]
  Creates an INSTANCE node, copies INSTANCE_SYNC_PROPS from the component, then clones
  all children (each child gets componentId pointing to its source child).

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.syncInstances(componentId) [2026-03-26]
  After a component is edited, propagates changes to all live instances.
  Skips fields present in instance.overrides. Calls syncChildren for child reconciliation.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.detachInstance(instanceId) [2026-03-26]
  Converts an INSTANCE to a FRAME, clearing componentId and overrides.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.resolveVariable(variableId, modeId?, visited?) -> VariableValue | undefined [2026-03-26]
  Looks up a variable's value for the active (or given) mode. Follows alias chains,
  guarding against cycles with a visited set.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.addVariable / removeVariable [2026-03-26]
  Add: registers variable and appends its id to the owning collection.
  Remove: deletes variable, removes from collection, and scrubs all node.boundVariables references.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.addCollection / removeCollection [2026-03-26]
  Add: registers collection and sets the default active mode.
  Remove: recursively removes all variables in the collection, then deletes collection and mode entry.

---

FUNCTION SceneGraph.flattenTree(parentId?, depth?) -> Array<{node, depth}> [2026-03-26]
  DFS pre-order traversal returning every node with its nesting depth. Used for layer list rendering.
